# Docker build context, allow-list style (issue #026): deny everything by
# default, then explicitly re-include only what the Dockerfile actually
# copies. Safer than a deny-list against secrets and dev-only material
# (.env, .kamal/secrets, .git, docs/, test/, .claude/) ever leaking into
# the build context by omission when a new file type is added later.
*

!mix.exs
!mix.lock
!config/
!config/**
!lib/
!lib/**
!priv/
!priv/**
!assets/
!assets/**
!rel/
!rel/**

# Re-excluded even though they live under a directory allowed above: built
# by the Dockerfile itself inside the image, never taken from the host
# (different architecture, different Elixir/OTP/Node versions than the
# host running `docker build`).
assets/node_modules/
priv/static/assets/
priv/static/cache_manifest.json

# Manually downloaded border datasets (`.gitignore`'s own note): never
# part of a release image, they are imported once via a mix task against
# a running database, not shipped in the application.
priv/data/
